OrganizationBusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: NEA FUND FOR CHILDREN & PUBLIC EDUCATION

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REGULATION SECTION 1.257-6E TRANSFERS THE NEBRASKA STATE EDUCATION ASSOCIATION COLLECTS POLITICAL CONTRIBUTIONS OR MEMBER DUES EARMARKED FOR A SEPARATE SEGREGATED FUND AND PROMPTLY AND DIRECTLY TRANSFERS THEM TO THAT FUND AS PRESCRIBED IN REGULATION SECTION 1.527-6E.
ORGANIZATION'S DIRECT AND INDIRECT POLITICAL CAMPAIGN ACTIVITIES NEBRASKA STATE EDUCATION ASSOCIATION HAS STAFF TIME TO COMMUNICATE TO MEMBERS REGARDING FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL CANDIDATES.

THE ASSOCIATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(5) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, EXCEPT ON NET INCOME DERIVED FROM UNRELATED BUSINESS ACTIVITIES. THE ASSOCIATION HAS ADVERTISING INCOME, WHICH IS SUBJECT TO TAX ON UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. FOR THE YEAR ENDED AUGUST 31, 2023, THE ASSOCIATION HAD NO TAX LIABILITY ON UNRELATED BUSINESS ACTIVITY. THE ASSOCIATION BELIEVES THAT IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NSEA HAS ACTIVE MEMBERS, RETIRED MEMBERS AND STUDENT MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ACTIVE MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION ELECT THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THEIR OFFICERS BY ONE PERSON EACH HAVING ONE VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DECISIONS OF THE GOVERNING BODY SUBJECT TO APPROVAL INCLUDE WHEN ANY MEMBER IS ELECTED AS A DELEGATE TO THE ANNUAL ASSEMBLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS DISTRIBUTED TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS AT A REGULARLY SCHEDULED BOARD MEETING FOR THEIR REVIEW. BASED ON THE BOARD'S DISCUSSION, CHANGES ARE MADE TO THE TAX RETURN PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE NSEA PRESDIENT, EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND COMPTROLLER ARE MADE AWARE OF ALL POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND ADDRESS THE CONFLICTS AND NOTIFY THE BOARD WHEN APPROPRIATE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. THE BOARD USES COMPENSATION SURVEY DATA FROM SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS IN OTHER STATES TO HELP SET THE COMPENSATION LEVEL FOR THE ORGANIZATION'S MANAGEMENT LEVEL EMPLOYEES. KEY EMPLOYEES' COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. THE BOARD USES COMPENSATION SURVEY DATA FROM SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS IN OTHER STATES TO HELP SET THE COMPENSATION LEVEL FOR THE ORGANIZATION'S MANAGEMENT LEVEL EMPLOYEES.
